=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Acylate tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-amine with 2,4-dichlorobenzoyl chloride (base, e.g. Et3N) to give the coupling partner N-(tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-yl)-2,4-dichlorobenzamide. | Step 2: From methyl 3-bromo-5-iodothiophene-2-carboxylate, do a selective Sonogashira coupling at I with tert-butylacetylene (Pd/Cu, amine base) to form methyl 3-bromo-5-(tert-butylethynyl)thiophene-2-carboxylate. | Step 3: Buchwald/Ullmann-type N-arylation of that bromothiophene with N-(tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-yl)-2,4-dichlorobenzamide to install the C3 N(C(O)Ar)(tetrahydropyranyl) group, giving methyl 5-(tert-butylethynyl)-3-[N-(2,4-dichlorobenzoyl)-N-(tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-yl)amino]thiophene-2-carboxylate. | Step 4: Hydrolyze the methyl ester (LiOH or NaOH, then acid workup) to reach CC(C)(C)C#Cc1cc(N(C(=O)c2ccc(Cl)cc2Cl)C2CCOCC2)c(C(=O)O)s1.

